SIMPLE: empty
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Empty
<hw>Emp"ty</hw> <pr>(?; 215)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Emptier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Emptiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>emtig</ets>, <ets>⟦ae⟧mtig</ets>, <ets>⟦ae⟧metig</ets>, fr.
<ets>⟦ae⟧mta</ets>, <ets>⟦ae⟧metta</ets>, quiet, leisure, rest; of
uncertain origin; cf. G. <ets>emsig</ets> busy.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Containing nothing; not holding or having anything within; void of
contents or appropriate contents; not filled; -- said of an inclosure,
or a container, as a box, room, house, etc.; <as>as, an <ex>empty</ex>
chest, room, purse, or pitcher; an <ex>empty</ex> stomach;
<ex>empty</ex> shackles.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 487 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Free; clear; devoid; -- often with
<xex>of</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧That fair female troop . . .
<xex>empty</xex> of all good.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall find you <qex>empty</qex> of that fault.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having nothing to carry; unburdened.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An
<xex>empty</xex> messenger.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When ye go ye shall not go <qex>empty</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. iii.
21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Destitute of effect, sincerity, or sense; -- said of
language; <as>as, <ex>empty</ex> words, or threats</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Words are but <qex>empty</qex> thanks.</q>
<rj><qau>Cibber.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Unable to satisfy; unsatisfactory; hollow; vain; --
said of pleasure, the world, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pleas'd in the silent shade with <qex>empty</qex> praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Producing nothing; unfruitful; -- said of a plant or
tree; <as>as, an <ex>empty</ex> vine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seven <qex>empty</qex> ears blasted with the east wind.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xli. 27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Destitute of, or lacking, sense, knowledge, or
courtesy; <as>as, <ex>empty</ex> brains; an <ex>empty</ex>
coxcomb.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That in civility thou seem'st so <qex>empty</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>Destitute of reality, or real existence;
unsubstantial; <as>as, <ex>empty</ex> dreams</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Empty</xex> is used as the first element in a
compound; as, <xex>empty</xex>-handed, having nothing in the hands,
destitute; <xex>empty</xex>-headed, having few ideas;
<xex>empty</xex>-hearted, destitute of feeling.</note></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Vacant</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Empty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Empty
<hw>Emp"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Empties</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>An empty box, crate, cask,
etc.; -- used in commerce, esp. in transportation of freight; <as>as,
⟦ldquo⟧special rates for <ex>empties</ex></as>.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Empty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Empty
<hw>Emp"ty</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Emptied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Emptying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To deprive of the contents; to
exhaust; to make void or destitute; to make vacant; to pour out; to
discharge; <as>as, to <ex>empty</ex> a vessel; to <ex>empty</ex> a well
or a cistern.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The clouds . . . <qex>empty</qex> themselves upon the earth.</q>
<rj><qau>Eccl. xi. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Empty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Empty
<hw>Emp"ty</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To discharge itself;
<as>as, a river <ex>empties</ex> into the ocean</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To become empty.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The chapel
<xex>empties</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>empty-bellied</ent>⟦br⟧
